The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Teacher shift order
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Teacher shift order
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Cuttack, Dec. 13: Acting on a PIL, seeking judicial intervention against uninterrupted posting of a teacher for 32 years in the same school, Orissa High Court has ordered immediate transfer of Sudhakar Tripathy.        
	Tripathy has been a Sanskrit teacher at Kalinga Nodal Upper Primary School at Choudwar since 1977.         
	At present, he is officiating as the acting headmaster of the school.         
	The court, in its order on Friday, further asked the school and mass education department to submit a compliance report by January 8 along with all documents and orders issued related to the service of the teacher.         
	Village education committee president Ratikant Patnaik had filed the PIL.                     
	Although transfer orders of the Sanskrit teacher was ordered on August 16, he had managed to continue in the school as acting headmaster.                                                                                                                                                          
